# Normalize line endings across platforms. openinfo is authored on macOS/Linux
# (LF), and several generated-artifact guards compare files byte-for-byte (e.g.
# the shared/contracts schema-drift test regenerates schemas/*.json and diffs
# them against the committed copies). On Windows with core.autocrlf=true a
# checkout would rewrite those committed files to CRLF, so the LF the generator
# emits no longer matches and the guard fails spuriously. Forcing LF on checkout
# keeps every text file identical on every OS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary types git must never touch.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.icns binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
